How will you check if a given Binary Tree is a Binary Search Tree or not?
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

To see if a binary tree is a binary search tree, check-
i)If a node is a left child, then its key and the keys of the nodes 
in its right subtree are less than its parent’s key.

ii)If a node is a right child, then its key and the keys of the nodes 
in its left subtree are greater than its parent’s key.